Uses of IStatistics in com.eim.utility.statistics.model
 

Classes in com.eim.utility.statistics.model that implement IStatistics
 class BenchmarkRelatedStatistics
          POJO representing the benchmark related statistics.

It is annotated with hibernate annotations for persistence purpose.
These statistics are persisted in the table STATS_BENCHMARK and identified using a sequence called SEQ_STATS_BENCHMARK.
 class ComputedStatistics
          POJO representing the non-benchmark related statistics.

It is annotated with hibernate annotations for persistence purpose.
These statistics are persisted in the table STATS_COMPUTED and identified using a sequence called SEQ_STATS_COMPUTED.

Method parameters in com.eim.utility.statistics.utility with type arguments of type IStatistics
static void HibernateUtil.storeStatistics(java.util.List<IStatistics> list, java.util.List<IStatistics> existing, java.lang.Class<?> storedClass)
          Store all the given statistics.
The method uses 2 lists the first one contains all the already existing statistics and the second one contains the newly computed statistics.
The method controls if a new statistics will replace an existing one.
